# Documentation Standards

## Documentation Structure

- Use clear headings and subheadings with proper hierarchy
- Include code examples where appropriate
- Reference specific files using [filename](/filename) syntax
- Maintain consistent formatting throughout
- Take markdown linter into account

## Content Guidelines

- Explain business logic and workflows clearly
- Document key design decisions and rationale
- Include sequence diagrams for complex flows
- Keep documentation up-to-date with code changes
- Reference relevant Splice API documentation

## File References

- Use `[filename](/filename)` for internal file references
- Use `[filename.ext](/path/to/filename.ext)` for files in subdirectories
- Reference external documentation with proper URLs

## Code Examples

- Include complete, runnable code examples
- Show both success and error scenarios
- Use syntax highlighting for Daml code blocks
- Include expected outputs where helpful

## Project Documentation

- [README.md](/README.md) - Main project overview and setup
- [WORKFLOW.md](/WORKFLOW.md) - Development workflow and processes
- Package-specific documentation in respective directories
